lenders.occupational_info: As a Child care provider I am responsible for the nurturing, teaching, and care of children who have not yet entered kindergarten. I also supervise older children before and after school. As a provider I play an important role in a child's development by caring for them when their parents are at work or are away for other reasons or when the parents place their children in care to help them socialize with children their age. In addition to attending to the child's health, safety, and nutrition, child care providers organize activities and implement curriculum that stimulates a child's physical, emotional, intellectual, and social growth. I help children explore individual interests, develop talents and independence, build self-esteem, learn how to get along with others, and prepare for more formal schooling. The things that people don't realize about most full-time providers is that they work about 60 to 70 hours a week helping children. Not only do they help children but they help parents. We train new parents on the care of their children, we train teenage parents on the care of their child. We become a resource for helping families in distress of all ages. Anyone can have a child but it takes a special person to be a parent.
